EbeyeParser Deprecated. use EbeyeSaxParser instead, this one requires lots of memory for big files.
EbeyeSaxParser Parser for EB-Eye XML files to populate a mega-map.
HibernateUtil Hibernate Utility class with a convenient method to get Session Factory object.
IntenzSaxParser Parser for IntEnzXML which extracts data interesting for the Enzyme Portal mega-map, namely cofactors, reactions, reactants and products as cross-references: EC number → Rhea reactions EC number → ChEBI entities (cofactors, substrates, products) Rhea reaction → ChEBI entities (reactants, products) Please note that in case of reversible (bidirectional) reactions - most of the enzyme classification - the relationship for ChEBI entities will be set to Relationship.is_substrate_or_product_of (for EC cross-reference) or Relationship.is_reactant_or_product_of (for Rhea cross-reference), while irreversible (unidirectional: left-to-right or right-to-left in Rhea speech) will have the more specific Relationship.is_substrate_of/Relationship.is_product_of (for EC cross-reference) or Relationship.is_reactant_of/Relationship.is_product_of (for Rhea cross-reference).
MmSaxParser An abstract class with common implementation for MmParsers.
Reference  
Uniprot2DiseaseParser Class to parse the file - either HTML or tab-delimited - containing a table of equivalences from UniProt accessions to OMIM IDs and MeSH terms.
UniprotSaxParser UniProt XML parser which takes into account only primary accessions, entry names (IDs), organisms, EC numbers and PDB codes, and indexes/stores them in a mega-map.
